            <section class="prose mt-8">
              <h2>How to use the timer calculator</h2>
              <h3>1. Add or subtract multiple time values</h3>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  Enter each duration in a separate row as hours, minutes, and
                  seconds.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Use the <strong>+</strong> or <strong>−</strong> selector to
                  choose whether that row is added or subtracted.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Click <strong>Calculate total</strong> to see the combined
                  result.
                </li>
              </ol>
              <p>
                The calculator automatically normalizes minutes and seconds
                (e.g. 90 minutes becomes 1 hour 30 minutes).
              </p>

              <h3>2. Read the result in different formats</h3>
              <p>After calculation you’ll see:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Total (hh:mm:ss)</strong> – standard time format,
                  including a minus sign if the result is negative.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Total seconds</strong> – useful for programming or
                  precise timing.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Decimal hours</strong> – ideal for timesheets and
                  billing (e.g. 1:30:00 → 1.5 hours).
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Decimal minutes</strong> – for quick mental math or
                  spreadsheets.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>3. Run a countdown timer</h3>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  Set the countdown duration in the
                  <strong>Countdown Timer</strong> panel.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Or click <strong>Load into countdown timer</strong> to use the
                  total from the calculator above.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Press <strong>Start</strong> to begin the countdown,
                  <strong>Pause</strong> to pause, and <strong>Reset</strong> to
                  go back to the original duration.
                </li>
              </ol>

              <h2>Time calculation formulas</h2>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <p><strong>1. Convert hh:mm:ss to seconds</strong></p>
                <p>\(\text{totalSeconds} = 3600 \times h + 60 \times m + s\)</p>
                <p><strong>2. Convert seconds back to hh:mm:ss</strong></p>
                <p>
                  \(h = \left\lfloor \dfrac{|\text{totalSeconds}|}{3600}
                  \right\rfloor\)<br />
                  \(m = \left\lfloor \dfrac{|\text{totalSeconds}| \bmod
                  3600}{60} \right\rfloor\)<br />
                  \(s = |\text{totalSeconds}| \bmod 60\)
                </p>
                <p>
                  If <code>totalSeconds &lt; 0</code>, prepend a minus sign to
                  the formatted time.
                </p>
                <p><strong>3. Decimal conversions</strong></p>
                <p>
                  \(\text{hoursDecimal} = \dfrac{\text{totalSeconds}}{3600}\)
                </p>
                <p>
                  \(\text{minutesDecimal} = \dfrac{\text{totalSeconds}}{60}\)
                </p>
              </div>

              <h2>Common use cases</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Timesheets & work hours</strong> – add up shifts,
                  breaks, and overtime, then convert to decimal hours for
                  payroll.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Study or practice sessions</strong> – track multiple
                  sessions across a day or week.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Sports & training</strong> – sum intervals, laps, or
                  sets; run countdowns for rest periods.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Cooking & productivity</strong> – stack multiple
                  timers and countdowns for tasks or pomodoro sessions.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h2>FAQ</h2>
              <h3>Does the calculator support negative times?</h3>
              <p>
                Yes. If subtractions exceed additions, the total becomes
                negative and is shown with a leading minus sign in all formats.
              </p>

              <h3>Is my data stored anywhere?</h3>
              <p>
                No. All calculations run in your browser. Nothing is sent to a
                server.
              </p>

              <h3>Can I copy the result?</h3>
              <p>
                Use the <strong>Copy hh:mm:ss</strong> button to copy the
                formatted result to your clipboard for use in emails,
                spreadsheets, or timesheets.
              </p>
